        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We propose to use ALMA in band 3 for several reasons. First, it has the largest available field of view for a single pointing. At 92 GHz the primary beam FWHM of roughly  1 arcmin is the best choice. This
frequency range in a compact array configuration also allows for the 5--6 arcsec resolution required to achieve a confused image. Additionally, the source count at this frequency has not been well measured, particularly at fainter flux densities.

We have requested the maximum bandwidth of 7.5 GHz, so as to maximize continuum sensitivity. We set our depth requirement to 8 microJy rms . According to our models, this should enable us to the regime where the instrument noise roughly equals the confusion noise, necessary to estimate the fainter counts. We have chosen to stay at a single frequency setting in order to obtain the maximum depth in the frequency range. 
</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
